Versus Collector, Amritsar and another CORAM: Present:- Mr. J.S. Parmar, Advocate, for the petitioner. Dismissed as withdrawn with liberty aforesaid. JUDGE .2.2012 sjks CHANDIGARH CWP No. 4677 of 2010 Date of Decision : 27.2.2012 Bikramjit Singh

Versus State of Punjab and others CORAM: Present:- Mr. S.C. Nagpal, Advocate, for the petitioner. Mr. Bhagwant Kishore Gupta, Senior DAG Punjab. None for the respondents No. 2 and 3. Learned counsel, after seeking instructions from the petitioner, wants to withdraw the present writ petition since the matter is pending before the Civil Court. Dismissed as withdrawn. JUDGE .2.2012 sjks CHANDIGARH CWP No. 2743 of 2012 Date of Decision : 15.2.2012 Maghar Singh Versus State of Punjab and others CORAM: Present:- Mr. Kehar Singh Hissowal, Advocate, for the petitioner. Learned counsel for the petitioner, after arguing for some time, states that petitioner has already made representations dated 9.11.2011 and .11.2011 (Annexures-P-5 and P-6) before the authorities concerned, which are still pending before it. Therefore, he wants to withdraw the present writ petition with liberty to pursue his remedy before the authorities concerned. Dismissed as withdrawn with liberty aforesaid. The authorities are directed to pass appropriate orders on the aforesaid representations (Annexures P-5 & P-6) within three months from the date of receipt of certified copy of this order. JUDGE .2.2012 sjks CHANDIGARH CM No. 1922 of 2012 in/and
